Linear Modelling of Teams (Avg. Goals Conceded)

Initial assumption: Teams which are only represented a few times are replaced by new teams with same level next season.

Load libraries

library(boot)
library(tidyverse)
library(broom)

Load data

df <- read.csv('grand_total_df.csv')

Show data

head(df)

Divide into modelling and test data

df_model <- df %>% 
            filter(season_home != '2015/2016')
df_test <- df %>% 
           filter(season_home == '2015/2016')

Pick out needed non-nominal variables Points and goals are removed as they effectively consist of other variables in the data

df_model <- df_model %>% 
      select(-X, -home_team_name, -season_home, -avg_total_goals, 
            -avg_goals_conceded_home, -avg_goals_conceded_away, -target_variable,
            -home_points, -away_points)

Fit linear model

model1 <- lm(avg_total_goals_conceded ~ .,
             data = df_model)

Summarize the model

summary(model1)

BOOTSTRAPPING (1) 
bs <- function(formula, data, indices){
  d <- data[indices, ] #allows boot to select sample
  fit <- lm(formula, data = d)
  return(coef(fit))
}
#Bootstrapping with 5000 replications
set.seed(200)
results <- boot(df_model, 
                statistic = bs,
                R = 5000,
                formula = formula(model1))

Plot distributions

for(i in 1:length(results$t0)){
  hist(results$t[,i], 
       freq = TRUE,
       main = variable.names(model1)[i])
}

Coefficients where histograms from bootstrapping are centered around 0 show lack of significance.

Coefficients clearly centered around 0: home_shotoff home_fouls home_r away_team_goal away_y2 away_poss away_corners away_r

MODELLING ROUND 2
We leave these variables out and model again
r model2 <- lm(avg_total_goals_conceded ~ . -home_shotoff -home_fouls -home_r -away_team_goal -away_team_goal -away_y2 -away_poss -away_corners -away_r, df_model)

#Bootstrapping with 5000 replications

MODELLING ROUND 3
Same as before. Drop these variables and model again
r model3 <- lm(avg_total_goals_conceded ~ . -home_shotoff -home_fouls -home_r -away_team_goal -away_team_goal -away_y2 -away_poss -away_corners -away_r -home_shoton -home_corners -away_shoton - away_shotoff -away_fouls, df_model)

MODELLING ROUND 4 
model4 <- lm(avg_total_goals_conceded ~ . -home_shotoff -home_fouls -home_r -away_team_goal
                                          -away_team_goal -away_y2 -away_poss -away_corners -away_r
                                          -home_shoton -home_corners -away_shoton - away_shotoff -away_fouls
                                          -home_y2 -away_y1,
             df_model)
BOOTSTRAPPING ROUND 4 
#Bootstrapping with 5000 replications
set.seed(200)
results <- boot(df_model, 
                statistic = bs,
                R = 5000,
                formula = formula(model4))

Plot distributions

for(i in 1:length(results$t0)){
  hist(results$t[,i], 
       freq = TRUE,
       main = variable.names(model4)[i])
}

TESTING THE MODEL

We will test the model on the data from the season 2015/2016 to evaluate the performance of the model. The error estimate will be the Mean Aboslute Error (MAE) as this allows us to estimate by how much our model is off on average from the actual number of goals conceded

MAE

[1] 0.2149888

We observe that the model on average predicts 0.2 average goals conceded from the true value.
